<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFE06A5FFD19956D1A6CBF5A" pageId="27" pageNumber="785" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFE06A5FFD19956D1A6CBF5A" blockId="27.[741,1332,662,1089]" lastBlockId="27.[122,1332,1095,3101]" pageId="27" pageNumber="785">
The placement of Vespertilioamongst other members of the 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFE06A5FFC3095021AB2B84E" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1821" box="[972,1202,859,892]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="801" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Vespertilioninae">Vespertilioninae</taxonomicName>
is uncertain with some genetic studies reporting the genus sister to what is recognized as Pipistrellini here and other reporting the genus sister to the rest of whatis 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFE06A5FFB5395A01D38BF73" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1821" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="993" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Vespertilionini">Vespertilionini</taxonomicName>
here. Further studies are needed to clarify the taxonomic position of the genus. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
